Greetings to Turkish President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 2 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Abdullah Gul on his election as President of Turkey on August 31. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the bilateral friendly relations would further develop on good terms, Kim in the message wished him success in his work for progress and prosperity of the country.

Greetings to Vietnamese President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, sent a message of greetings to Nguyen Minh Triet, President of Vietnam, today on the occasion of its 62nd national day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam, in the message, sincerely wished the president and people of Vietnam greater success in their work to build socialist Vietnam under the leadership of the Communist Party of Vietnam and expressed the belief that the traditional friendly and cooperative relations between the two peoples would grow stronger.

Greetings to Slovak President  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Ivan Gasparovic, President of the Slovak Republic, today on the occasion of the day of its constitution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim in the message expressed belief that the bilateral ties would expand and develop in the mutual interests and wished the Slovak people happiness.

Visits 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- A DPRK delegation led by Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun left Pyongyang Saturday to participate in the ministerial meeting of the non-aligned movement on human rights and cultural diversity to be held in Tehran and to visit Iran. A friendship delegation of North Hwanghae Province led by Chairman of North Hwanghae Provincial People's Committee Ri Sang Gwan also left Pyongyang today to visit Mongolia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Arriving here on the same day was a delegation of the International Cultural and Educational Foundation of Nepal led by President Ek Nath Dhakal and a delegation of Loxley Pacific Company Limited of Thailand led by Jingjai Hanchanlash, executive vice-president of the Loxley Public Company Limited of Thailand, to participate in the 22nd meeting of the Northï¿½|East Asia Telephone and Telecommunications Co. LTD Directors' Board.

Wreaths Laid before Grave of Kim Po Hyon 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 2 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the grave of ardent patriot Kim Po Hyon in Mangyongdae on Sunday on the occasion of the 52nd anniversary of his demise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen before the grave was a wreath sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Choe Thae Bok, Choe Yong Rim, officials of the party, armed forces and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, KPA servicepersons and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths were placed before the grave in the name of the WPK Central Committee, ministries, national institutions, educational and media organs, the Mangyongdae Revolutionary School and party and power organs and farms in the city.

National Day of DPRK Observed  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 2 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held in Switzerland and round-table talks in the Czech Republic on Aug. 24 and 25 to mark the 59th founding anniversary of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Martin Lotscher, chairman of the Swiss-Korea Committee, said at the meeting that the DPRK has demonstrated its might all over the world as man-centered socialist country under the wise guidance of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The executive secretary of the Central Committee of the Czech, Moravian, Silesian Trade Unions' Association and the chairman of a county committee of the Communist Party of Czech and Moravia said at the round-table talks that the foundation of the DPRK by President Kim Il Sung marked a historical event which helped it to become a powerful socialist country, adding that the DPRK has been further developed by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting held in Switzerland.

GNP's Foolish Talk Condemned  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 2 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification reportedly issued a statement on August 22 in which it dismissed the group of the Grand National Party of south Korea letting loose a string of balderdash slandering the north-south summit meeting as a treacherous party standing against reunification while being keen on pursuing hostile policy toward the north only, quite indifferent to the interests of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the GNP comes to power the process for peace and reunification on the Korean Peninsula will be held in check, the statement said, stressing the need for the people to pool their efforts to throw the traitors of the anti-reunification political party to the dumping ground of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day, Minjok Thongsin, the internet newspaper of Koreans in the U.S., carried an article denouncing the balderdash of the GNP group slandering the north-south summit meeting.

Kim Jong Il's Songun Revolutionary Exploits Praised  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- A seminar and film shows were held in Democratic Congo and Russia on Aug. 21 on the occasion of the 47th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's start of Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the functions were photos showing the Songun leadership exploits of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants of the film shows watched Korean film "Korean People's Army, Steel-like Ranks".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Youth Group for the Study of the Juche Idea in Democratic Congo and other speakers at the seminar on the theme of "On the Songun politics of leader Kim Jong Il" said that the Songun idea and the Songun politics serve as powerful weapon for the world progressives aspiring after an independent and peaceful new world, adding that the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il is the best independent politics and a socialist political mode. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After watching the film, the chairman of the Russian Federation for the Development of Friendship and Cooperation with Foreign Countries noted that the KPA has grown to be revolutionary armed forces capable of defeating any powerful enemy under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, adding that the U.S. which arbitrarily behaves in the world arena as it pleases dares not provoke the DPRK.

Russian Poet Praises Kim Jong Il
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- A Russian poet Viktor Sharkov made public poem titled "Brilliant Image of Kim Jong Il." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said in his poem that the DPRK, advancing guided by the principle of Juche and the Korean nation-first spirit, boasts the unbreakable unity between the leader and people, adding that the imperialists and their servants would be stunned by the might of the DPRK and doomed to be forlorn wandering spirits in face of the firm will of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that no one on earth can overpower this tremendous strength of the DPRK, adding that Kim Jong Il is a lodestar of the glorious struggle always indicating the way before it.

U.S.-S. Korean Joint Military Exercises Denounced in India 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- The Indian Institute for Foreign Policy Studies made public a statement on Aug. 27 assailing the U.S.-south Korean "Ulji Focus Lens" joint military exercises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said that the U.S. forces present in south Korea for the last more than six decades are the stumbling block lying in the way of achieving peace and defusing tension on the Korean Peninsula, adding that peace and security on the Korean Peninsula and reunification of Korea are unattainable as long as the U.S. troops are allowed to stay there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should stop the military exercises and quit south Korea at once taking with it all combat equipment including nuclear weapons, demanded the statement.

Venezuelan President Supports Struggle of Korean Youth and Other People 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- It is my hope that the Korean youth and other people, united close around their supreme Kim Jong Il, will register bigger success in their struggle for the accomplishment of the cause of Korean-style socialism. Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez Frias said this on August 26 when meeting and conversing with a delegation of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League participating in the celebrations of the 60th anniversary of the movement of the World Festival of Youth and Students held in Venezuela. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We feel grateful to the DPRK for having expressed support and solidarity with the Bolivar socialist revolution of the Venezuelan people, he said, adding that they are following with deep attention the changes taking place on the Korean Peninsula.

Latin American Regional Seminar on Juche Idea Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- A Latin American regional seminar on the Juche idea was held in Ecuador on August 26 on the theme of "Let's build socialism in 21st century under banner of independence and peace".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Alva Chavez, chairperson of the Latin American Institute of the Juche Idea, in a report at the seminar said that President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il published many famous works and accumulated precious experience in the struggle for independence against imperialism and for socialism, thus instilling the profound truth of the Juche idea into the people of the Latin American countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A particular mention should be made of the fact that Kim Jong Il has wisely led the struggle of the Korean people with his unique Songun politics under the complicated international situation in the 1990s, she said, stressing that the Songun politics serves as a powerful treasured sword as it provides a sure guarantee for the victory of not only the socialist cause in the DPRK but the human cause of independence in view of the U.S. high-handed and arbitrary practices and moves for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing full support to the just stand of the DPRK on the nuclear issue, she noted that to voice solidarity with the Korean people not only constitutes an important way of shattering the outrageous high-handed practices and moves for aggression of the U.S. imperialists at present but means defending the independent right of the people in Latin American countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Delegates of Juche idea study organizations from Nicaragua, Peru, Venezuela, Mexico and Ecuador in their speeches renewed their determination to deepen the study and dissemination of the Juche idea, apply it in keeping with the specific conditions of Latin American countries and put the struggle for socialist construction in the 21st century on a higher stage and thereby make positive contributions to the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar.

Reception Given by Malaysian Charge d'Affaires 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- Jamal Sharifuddin Bin Johan, charge d'affaires ad interim in the DPRK, gave a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps Friday on the occasion of the 50th national day of Malaysia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, officials concerned and diplomatic envoys of foreign countries and representatives of international organizations here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were staff members of the Malaysian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

North-Targeted War Exercises Protested in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- Members of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification reportedly held a fierce demonstration in front of the "commanding control office" of the south Korea-U.S. "Combined Forces Command" on August 29. They barred a car carrying the commander of the U.S. forces in south Korea from moving. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The demonstrators charged that the "Ulji Focus Lens" joint military exercises were the north-targeted war drills staged in accordance with the "OPLAN 5027" aimed at the "collapse of the north".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. forces painted the military exercises as "annual defense drills" but their aggressive nature has been brought into bolder relief, they said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that such protest would continue in front of the "commanding control office".

Stronger NAM Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- The DPRK will fully discharge its responsibility and role as a dignified member of the non-aligned movement (NAM) in order to firmly maintain the fundamental principle, idea and purity of the movement and steadily strengthen and develop it, says Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed article dedicated to the day of the NAM. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The emergence of the NAM, a great anti-imperialist revolutionary force in the era of independence, and its development have brought about a great change in the balance of forces between progress and reaction in the international arena and gave a powerful impetus to the process of global independence, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The times steadily change and develop and in this course there emerge unpredictable grave obstacles and challenges. The NAM is faced with a heavy task to maintain its idea and fully discharge its mission to cope with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The NAM must continue holding aloft the banner of independence against imperialism and peace against war. Herein lies the key to the victorious advance of the movement. Only when the non-aligned and other developing countries intensify the struggle to defend peace against imperialism can they consolidate national independence, achieve independent development and progress and attain the noble idea and purpose of the movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The non-aligned countries should firmly unite and solidarize with one another politically on the principle of independence. Only when they maintain independence can they defend the dignity and interests of the countries and nations, achieve independent development and prosperity and consolidate unity and solidarity among countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an important way of consolidating unity and solidarity and solving difficult and complicated problems arising in building new societies for the non-aligned countries to closely cooperate with one another in the economic and technological fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Just is the idea and principle of the NAM. No one can block its victorious advance.

Ryongnam Hill Tells Kim Jong Il's Firm Pledge
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- Ryongnam Hill is a significant place where Kim Jong Il made a firm pledge to shine Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He, who matriculated at Kim Il Sung University, climbed up Ryongnam Hill on September 1, Juche 49 (1960) to make public his famous poem "Korea, I Will Glorify Thee" carrying his unswerving faith and will to exalt the brilliance of Korea for all ages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 True to his pledge, he has conducted energetic revolutionary activities for the protection of the ideas and cause of President Kim Il Sung and for the prosperity and happiness of the country and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has realized the single-minded unity, the great foundation of the revolution, in the course of wisely leading the efforts for transforming the whole society after the Juche idea and has glorified Korea as the eternal home of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, in the middle of the 1990s when the destiny of Korea was challenged by the moves of the imperialists to stifle the DPRK, he held aloft the banner of Songun and thus turned the unfavorable circumstances into favorable ones and the misfortune into the blessing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He defended the destiny of the country and people with the Korean People's Army as the pillar and main force of revolution and let the entire people learn from the revolutionary soldier spirit borne by the Songun era so as to effect a great change in the socialist construction as a whole. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the ten years from 1995 to 2004, tens of thousands of objects were commissioned or constructed, the arable land was realigned into large standardized fields throughout the country and great edifices were built in different parts of the country. All these were miracles to be lauded in the 5,000-year history of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As he pledged on Ryongnam Hill, leader Kim Jong Il continues his inspection tour of army units and factories and farms and brings about epoch-making changes on this land. His great exploits will shine long along with the prospering Songun Korea.

Exhibition of Paintings and Calligraphic Works of Former Unconverted Long-term Prisoners Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hyesan, September 1 (KCNA) -- An exhibition of paintings and calligraphic works of former unconverted long-term prisoners who are indomitable pro-reunification patriotic fighters was held at the Ryanggang Provincial Art Theatre from Aug. 27 to Sept. 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on display in the exhibition were more than 200 paintings and calligraphic works done by Choe Ha Jong, Choe Son Muk, An Yong Gi, Kim Un Hwan, Yang Jong Ho and Ri Kyong Chan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such works as "Eternal President of Republic," "Long Live General Kim Jong Il, Sun of 21st Century!" and "We Will Win As Long As There Is the Great General, Illustrious Commander Born of Heaven" truthfully depicted the personality of the generals of Mt. Paektu as great men born of Heaven, their immortal exploits and transparent ideological and moral world of the unconverted long-term prisoners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on display in the exhibition were calligraphic works such as "Songun Politics," "Long Journey of Songun Leadership," "Devoted Defence" and "Carrying Out the Leader's Instructions at Cost of Their Lives." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The former unconverted long-term prisoners produced paintings and calligraphic works showing the true appearance of Songun Korea and the unanimous desire of the Koreans for reunification.

15th Meeting of Executive Committee of Latin American Institute of Juche Idea Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- The 15th Meeting of the Executive Committee of the Latin American Institute of the Juche Idea was held in Ecuador on August 26. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting reviewed the work in the past period, discussed the orientation of future activities and reorganized the Executive Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jose Francisco Aguilar Bulgarelli was elected honorary chairman of the institute and Alva Chavez chairperson of the institute.

Japanese Authorities' Suppression of Chongryon under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 2 (KCNA) -- The World Federation of Democratic Youth (WFDY) terms the Japanese authorities' discrimination against Koreans in Japan and their moves to physically eliminate the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) huge human rights abuses wantonly violating the existing international laws on human rights including the UN Charter and the World Declaration of Human Rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WFDY said this in its statement on August 22 denouncing the Japanese authorities' suppression of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has an obligation to protect and ensure the democratic national rights and right to existence of Koreans in Japan both in view of historical facts and from political and moral points of view. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the Japanese authorities have openly revealed their attempt to obliterate Chongryon, far from repenting of and making apology and compensation for their blood-woven past. It is a mean act of evading their responsibility and grave perfidy to the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WFDY categorically rejects Japan's behavior as a dangerous and criminal act of further worsening the relations among countries and impairing peace and security in the Asia-Pacific region as it is an outrageous act of infringing upon the sovereignty of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WFDY appeals to all its members and friendly international, regional and national youth and students' organizations to express support and solidarity to the just struggle of Chongryon, the Korean Youth League in Japan and Koreans in Japan.

Kim Jong Il Provides Field Guidance to Different Units
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 2 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il provided field guidance to different units in Songgan and Jonchon counties of Jagang Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first leg of his guidance was the February General Steel Enterprise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He visited the revolutionary museum of the enterprise before going round several production processes to acquaint himself in detail with its technological equipment and production there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the feats performed by the workers and technicians of the enterprise in dynamically pushing ahead with the modernization of the steel enterprise, expressing great satisfaction over the fact that they are mass-producing quality steel, while cutting down the electricity consumption norm by actively introducing advanced technology and inventing and manufacturing various types of equipment by themselves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth the tasks to be fulfilled by the enterprise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the need for the enterprise to make an effective use of the existing foundation for production and continue energetically pushing forward the technological updating in order to boost the production of iron and steel. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent policy of the WPK to firmly establish Juche in the metallurgical industry, he said, calling for thoroughly establishing the steel production system based on Juche steel. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he went round the supply service facilities of the enterprise built in peculiar style. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The next leg of his guidance was the Jonchon Rock-Drill Factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He looked round the monument to the on-the-spot guidance given by President Kim Il Sung and the room devoted to the history of the factory before dropping in at the processing workshop to familiarize himself with the production there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the feats performed by the workers of the factory, noting that they have produced many quality rock-drills and supplied them to different fields of the national economy in the past, thus making a great contribution to the nation's economic development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After making the rounds of the combined stock farm and other supply service bases, he said that they have been built well to bring benefits to the workers and appreciated the way they are managing their economic life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He put forward the tasks to be carried out by the factory, saying that lots of rock-drills are required to further develop the mining industry and build roads and hydropower stations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last leg of his visit was the Jonchon County Commercial Management Office. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He looked round the monument to the on-the-spot guidance given by the President to the office and the room for the education in the revolutionary history, guided by Jong Chun Sil, director of the office. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He recollected with deep emotion the profound loving care and benevolence shown by the President for Jong Chun Sil and the office. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that Jong Chun Sil has grown to be a recipient of "Kim Il Sung Order" and twice labor hero well-known to the whole country and loved by the people amid the particular trust and loving care of the President, he told her to always bear deep in mind the President's noble wish to see her remaining a faithful servant for the people all her life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He visited the Jonchon manufactured goods shop to learn about how it is using the "Memo-book of our family" introduced by Jong decades ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not easy to meet the requirements of inhabitants for goods without fail at present when they are in short supply, he said, adding that this suffices to guess what noble and pure sense of moral obligation she has towards the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The posture and attitude of a soldier and disciple of the President should always remain unchanged as is the case with Jong, he said, stressing the need for the party members and other working people to learn from her intense loyalty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a souvenir picture taken with Jong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the expectation and conviction that the party members and other working people of Jagang Province would play the role of vanguard and shock brigade in all fields of socialist economic construction with the same vim and vigor with which they took the lead in weathering out the difficulties before the revolution in the revolutionary spirit of fortitude. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Pak To Chun, chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial Committee of the WPK.

Kim Jong Il Provides Field Guidance to Industrial Establishments
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 1 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il provided field guidance to industrial establishments in Manpho City. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first leg of his guidance was the Manpho Smeltery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He familiarized himself with the technological updating of the smeltery and production there, going round several production processes including the general production command room. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned about the technical principle and capacities of the updated production equipment. He highly appreciated the feats performed by the workers in the smeltery and members of the scientists and technicians' shock brigade of Kim Chaek University of Technology, expressing great satisfaction over the fact that they have completed modern and efficient smelting processes in a short span of time by introducing ultra-modern science and technology true to the Workers' Party of Korea's idea of attaching importance to science to boost the production of quality non-ferrous metals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the experience of the smeltery eloquently proves that technological progress is the master key to increasing production, adding: The major task facing the smeltery is to actively introduce advanced technology, while keeping production going on at a high rate, and thus steadily raise the actual extraction rate and retrieve all valuable metals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to mine and process a large amount of ores and supply more quality concentrated ores to the smeltery in time in order to operate it in full capacity, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The next leg of his guidance was the Amnokgang Tyre Plant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned in detail about technical equipment of the plant and production there, making the rounds of moulding workshops, finishing workshop and other production processes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Watching for a long while with delight various kinds of quality tyres streaming out of every worksite equipped with modern equipment, he was greatly pleased to learn that the workers of the plant have kept the production going at a high rate after radically changing its appearance by fully displaying the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance and fortitude. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 How gratifying it is to see the plant sharply boosting its production and its workers working with ease in a good production environment as a result of the successful modernization of the plant, he noted. He praised the officials, workers and technicians of the plant for having devoted themselves to the work to bring about such signal change and highly appreciated their successes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was very pleased to hear that the discharged soldiers who volunteered to work at the plant in hearty response to the Party's call have played a key role in the production and construction after becoming junior cadres and skilled workers and the fighting spirit of all the employees has remarkably gone up.  It is the precious success which cannot be bartered for anything that the position of the working class has grown stronger in the course of pulling through rigorous ordeals, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he looked round the room for the education in the revolutionary history, the room for the study of the reminiscences of President Kim Il Sung, a canteen, a store for what they produced through sideline farming and other facilities for ideological and cultural education and supply service to learn in detail about the political work and supply service for the workers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised the shining successes made by the workers of the plant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be fulfilled by the plant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need to continue to pay deep attention to the matter of putting the production on a normal track, he called for increasing the production of tyres to suit the actual conditions of the country. He stressed the need to establish a synthetic rubber production system for the purpose of finding a satisfactory solution to the problem of rubber, the main raw material for the production, in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the plant has a solid material and technological foundation for steadily boosting the production and very high zeal of its workers, he underlined the need for the officials to more scrupulously organize the economic work on the principle of profitability in keeping with this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He showed profound love and solicitude for the workers of the plant, calling for providing better living conditions to the workers and always taking deep care of them as they have devoted their all to the Party and the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing satisfaction over the fact that the workers in Manpho City are working and living in a revolutionary manner after sprucing up not only factories but urban and rural areas to meet the need of socialism, he praised the Korean working class as a large revolutionary contingent intensely loyal to the Party and the leader and strong in organization and discipline. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Pak To Chun, chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial Committee of the WPK.

Corea cumplira con su deber para el desarrollo del NOAL
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 1 de septiembre (ATCC) -- El periodico Rodong Sinmun inserto en su numero de este sabado un articulo individual dedicado al Dia de la No Alineacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, como digno pais miembro del movimiento de los no alineados (NOAL) cumplira con toda su responsabilidad y papel para salvaguardar el principio fundamental, el ideal y la pureza de este movimiento y desarrollarlo de continuo, senala el articulo y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La aparicion y el fortalecimiento del NOAL que es la potente fuerza revolucionaria antiimperialista de la epoca de independencia imprimieron gran cambio a la correlacion de las fuerzas entre el progreso y la reaccion en la escena internacional y promovieron con vigor el proceso de realizacion de la independencia en el mundo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Con el tiempo que transcurre aparecen sin cesar los graves obstaculos y desafios imprevistos que obligan al movimiento no alineado a asumir la importante tarea de defender su ideal y cumplir con su mision. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El NOAL debe seguir enarbolando la bandera de independencia antiimperialista y de la paz antibelica. He aqui la llave para el avance victorioso de este movimiento. Solo al fortalecer la lucha antiimperialista por la defensa de la paz, los paises no alineados y en vias de desarrollo pueden  consolidar la independencia nacional, lograr el desarrollo independiente y el progreso del pais y realizar el noble ideal y objetivo del NOAL. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los paises no alineados deben unirse y solidarizarse en lo politico en el principio de la independencia. Solo cuando mantengan la independencia, es posible defender la dignidad e intereses del pais y la nacion, lograr el desarrollo y la prosperidad independientes y consolidar la unidad y solidaridad entre los paises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La estrecha cooperacion economica y tecnica de los paises no alineados deviene un importante medio para fortalecer la unidad y solidaridad del NOAL y resolver los problemas dificiles y complicados que se presentan en la construccion de una nueva sociedad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Son justas el ideal y el principio del NOAL. Nadie puede impedir el avance victorioso de este movimiento.

Simposio regional latinoamericano sobre la idea Juche en Ecuador
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 1 de septiembre (ATCC) -- Tuvo lugar el 26 de agosto en Ecuador el simposio regional latinoamericano sobre la idea Juche que tuvo por su agenda "Construyamos el socialismo del siglo 21 bajo la bandera de la independencia y la paz".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La presidenta del Instituto Latinoamericano para el Estudio de la Idea Juche, Alba Chavez, presento el informe de la ocasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La oradora senalo que el Presidente Kim Il Sung y el Dirigente Kim Jong Il infundieron la profunda verdad de la idea Juche en los pueblos latinoamericanos al publicar numerosas obras clasicas y crear valiosas experiencias de la lucha por la independencia antiimperialista y el socialismo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Prosiguio que en particular, Su Excelencia Kim Jong Il condujo sabiamente la lucha del pueblo coreano con su original politica de Songun (priorizacion militar) aun bajo la complicada situacion de la decada de 1990. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Destaco que la politica de Songun deviene un medio poderosisimo que asegura con firmeza no solo la causa socialista de Corea sino tambien la victoria de la causa de independencia de la humanidad frente al despotismo, arbitrariedades y maniobras de agresion de Estados Unidos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tras expresar irrestricto apoyo a la justa posicion de la RPDC en cuanto al problema nuclear, insistio en que la solidaridad con el pueblo coreano resulta en la epoca actual un importante remedio para frustrar las brutales maniobras despoticas y agresivas de los imperialistas norteamericanos y significa la defensa de los derechos soberanos de los pueblos latinoamericanos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le siguieron en usar la palabra los delegados de las organizaciones de estudio de la idea Juche de Nicaragua, Peru, Venezuela, Mexico y Ecuador quienes exteriorizaron sus determinaciones de profundizar el estudio y la divulgacion de la idea Juche y materializarla segun las condiciones reales de los paises latinoamericanos para desplegar en una etapa mas alta la lucha por construir el socialismo del siglo 21 y contribuir de esta manera a la realizacion de la causa de independencia de todo el mundo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el foro se aprobo una carta destinada al Dirigente Kim Jong Il.

Sesionada XV reunion del comite ejecutivo del ILEIJ
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 1 de septiembre (ATCC) -- Sesiono el 26 de agosto en Ecuador la XV reunion del comite ejecutivo del Instituto Latinoamericano para el Estudio de la Idea Juche (ILEIJ). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion se hizo balance del trabajo de los tiempos anteriores, se debatio el rumbo de las actividades de lo adelante y se recompuso el comite ejecutivo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Jose Francisco Aguilar Bulgarelli y Alba Chavez fueron designados como presidente honorario y presidenta del ILEIJ.
